==English==

===Etymology===
Coined by the video game community and opponents of the lockout practice. The practice originated with the video game community and was devised by the video game company [[Nintendo]].

===Noun Phrase===
'''regional lockout'''

The programming practice, code, or chip used to prevent the playing of imported media on a domestically marketed device.

